RCB's openers set the tone for the innings. Phil Salt led the charge with a blistering 56 off 31 balls while Virat Kohli playing his 400th T20 match remained unbeaten on 59 from 36 deliveries. Skipper Rajat Patidar added a quickfire 34 off 16 balls and Liam Livingstone sealed the victory with an explosive 15* off just 5 balls. RCB reached the target comfortably in 16.2 overs finishing at 177/3.
